4. Coding Conventions

Across all modules, the scripts enforce consistent conventions:

Primary key

EA_ID – Enumeration Area identifier (stored as character for merging across files).

Binary variables

All binary variables use a strict 1/0 coding:

1 = Yes / Presence / True / Problem exists

0 = No / Absence / False

Original GLSS coding (e.g., 1 = Yes, 2 = No) is recoded to 1/0.

In ties when aggregating to EA-level, presence (1) is used as the tie-breaker.

Aggregation level

All community-level information is collapsed to one row per EA_ID.

Missing data

Some continuous or heavily missing variables are dropped if >1/3 of observations are missing.

For a subset of binary variables, NA is later set to 0 when conceptually interpreted as “no problem / no presence reported” at the EA level.

5. Module Details
5.1. cs0.dta – Community Heterogeneity

Purpose: Construct an EA-level dummy capturing whether the EA contains multiple distinct communities.

Key steps:

5.1. cs1.dta – Population by EA

Purpose: Aggregate population counts to EA level.

Key steps:

Load cs1.dta.

Check missingness for region, district, eanum, and original population variable s1q1.

Remove exact duplicate rows.

Rename s1q1 → population.

Drop region and district, keeping only eanum and population.

Aggregate by eanum (EA):

TOTAL_POPULATION = sum(population, na.rm = TRUE).

Rename eanum → EA_ID.

Convert EA_ID to character.

Check for NAs in EA_ID and TOTAL_POPULATION.

Label variables (EA_ID, TOTAL_POPULATION).

Save as: cs1_cleaned.dta.

5.2. cs2.dta – Infrastructure, Markets, Migration & Projects

Purpose: Build EA-level indicators for infrastructure, markets, transport, migration, living standards, and community projects.

Key concepts:

Standardization: all GLSS binary 1 = Yes, 2 = No are converted to "1"/"0" (strings) then to numeric 1/0.

Custom modal aggregation:

A custom_modal_aggregator() chooses the most frequent category, with 1 preferred when a tie occurs in 0/1 variables.

Key steps:

Load & prepare

Read cs2.dta.

Rename IDs: region → REGION_ID, district → DISTRICT_ID, eanum → EA_ID.

Convert key categorical columns (IDs and multiple-response fields) to character.

Clean and binary recoding

Keep only relevant columns (IDs + infrastructure, markets, migration, project codes).

Remove exact duplicates.

Use helper to_binary_01() to recode 1/2 questions to "1" / "0".

Construct derived binary variables:

is_farming_major – farming appears in any of top 4 economic activities.

migration_out_agric, migration_in_agric.

living_improved_binary – living conditions improved vs same/worse.

work_increased_binary – work increased vs not.

Expand major project codes (s2q38a, s2q38b, s2q38c) into separate dummies:

proj_type_1_school, proj_type_2_health, … , proj_type_9_other.

EA-level aggregation

Group by REGION_ID, DISTRICT_ID, EA_ID.

For each EA, compute:

Binary modal indicators (0/1) for:

farming_major_modal

motorable_road_access, road_impassable_binary

has_electricity_any, has_piped_water_any, has_post_office_phone

has_bank, has_permanent_market, has_periodic_market

public_transport_passes, seasonal_out_migration_agric, seasonal_in_migration_agric

living_improved_modal, work_increased_or_not_modal

proj_type_1_school_modal … proj_type_9_other_modal

Mean EA-level distances:

dist_to_road_km

dist_to_major_market_km

dist_to_transport_catch_km

Convert 0/1 strings to numeric, clean NaN distances.

Missing data filtering & imputation

Drop high-missingness variables:

dist_to_road_km, dist_to_transport_catch_km,

seasonal_in_migration_agric, dist_to_major_market_km.

Impute remaining NAs for:

has_periodic_market, seasonal_out_migration_agric using their modal value 0 (treat missing as "No").

Save final EA-level file as: cs2_cleaned.dta.

5.3. cs3.dta – Education & Adult Literacy

Purpose: Construct EA-level indicators for school presence, enrollment levels, and schooling barriers.

Key steps:

Dedup & select

Load cs3.dta, remove exact duplicates.

Keep:

IDs: region, district, eanum.

School presence: s3q1 (primary), s3q11 (JSS), s3q20 (SSS).

Enrollment categories: s3q8 (boys primary), s3q9 (girls primary), s3q19 (JSS), s3q28 (SSS).

Adult literacy program: s3q29.

Non-attendance reasons: s3q10a–s3q10c.

Rename to descriptive variables and drop region and district.

Missingness and binary recoding

Summarize missingness; drop non-reason variables with >30% NA (if any).

Recode presence questions (school/program) from 1/2 to 1/0.

Reason dummies

Collapse Q10 reason codes (1–8) into binary dummies:

reason_cost, reason_no_interest_parents, reason_no_interest_children,
reason_school_far, reason_inadequate_facility, reason_dangerous_route,
reason_child_labour, reason_other.

EA aggregation

Define:

mode_yes_priority() – binary modal with YES as tie-breaker.

mode_enrolment() – modal enrollment category (with highest category used in ties).

Group by EA_ID and compute:

School presence (binary modal):

primary_school_present, jss_present, sss_present, adult_literacy_program.

Enrollment levels (1–6):

primary_enrol_boys_level, primary_enrol_girls_level,
jss_enrol_level, sss_enrol_level.

Schooling barriers (binary modal):

reason_cost_modal, reason_no_interest_parents_modal,
reason_no_int_children_modal, reason_school_far_modal,
reason_inadequate_facility_modal, reason_dangerous_route_modal,
reason_child_labour_modal, reason_other_modal.

Barrier NA handling

Replace NA in barrier dummies with 0 at EA-level (treated as “barrier not salient in this EA”).

Save as: cs3_cleaned.dta.

5.4. cs4a.dta – Health Worker Access

Purpose: Capture EA-level access to different types of health providers and distance to care.

Key concepts:

s4aq0 – provider type (1–9).

s4aq1 – presence (1 Yes, 2 No → recoded to 1/0).

s4aq2 – distance (km) to nearest such provider.

Provider groupings:

General health providers:

doctor, nurse, pharmacist, community health worker, medical assistant.

Maternal/pregnancy providers:

midwife, family planning worker.

Key steps:

Remove duplicates and drop region, district, and time variables.

Recode s4aq1 to 1/0.

Reconstruct community_id within each EA:

Communities are inferred from sequences of provider codes; s4aq0 == 9 marks the end of each community block.

At EA × community level, compute:

Min distance to any general provider: general_min_dist_comm.

Min distance to any maternal provider: maternal_min_dist_comm.

Access flags: general_access_comm, maternal_access_comm.

At EA level, compute:

general_health_access (1 if any community has general_access_comm = 1).

maternal_health_access (1 if any community has maternal_access_comm = 1).

gen_healthaccess_dist_km – mean of per-community min distances (general).

maternal_healthaccess_dist_km – mean of per-community min distances (maternal).

Distance means set to NA if no valid distances exist.

Create access index categories:

general_health_access_index:

"Facility in EA", "Nearby (<=5km)", "Distant (>5km)", "Access Unknown".

maternal_health_access_index:

"Maternity Care in EA", "Nearby (<=5km)", "Distant (>5km)", "Access Unknown".

Save as: cs4a_cleaned.dta.

5.5. cs4b.dta – Health Facilities

Purpose: Capture EA-level presence and distance to health facilities: general, maternal, and medicine sources.

Key facility groups:

General health facilities: hospital, clinic/health post.

Maternal facilities: maternity home, family planning clinic.

Medicine access: drugstore / chemical store, pharmacy.

Key steps:

Load cs4b.dta, remove duplicates.

Drop region, district, time to facility, year established, and dispensary indicators (distance-based focus).

Recode s4bq5 (facility presence) from 1/2 to 1/0.

Reconstruct community_id within EA by cumulative sum of s4bq0 == 15.

At EA × community level, compute:

general_min_dist_comm, maternal_min_dist_comm, medicine_min_dist_comm.

general_access_comm, maternal_access_comm, medicine_access_comm.

At EA level, compute:

Presence dummies:

general_health_facility, maternal_health_facility, medicine_access_facility (1 if any community has access).

Distances:

general_health_distance_km

maternal_health_distance_km

medicine_distance_km (mean of community minima, NA if no data).

Save as: cs4b_cleaned.dta.

5.6. cs4c.dta – Health Context & Disease Environment

Purpose: Construct EA-level dummies for major diseases, health service problems, campaigns, and birth location.

Key steps:

Load cs4c.dta, remove exact duplicates.

Select and rename:

EA_ID, health problem codes (top 4), health service problem codes (top 4),

birth_location_raw, imm_campaign_raw, antimal_campaign_raw.

Drop region, district.

Recode campaign questions:

imm_campaign_5yr, antimal_campaign_5yr (1/2 → 1/0).

Create disease dummies (dis_*) using top 4 health problem codes:

dis_malaria, dis_hernia, dis_guinea_worm, dis_bilharzia,
dis_measles, dis_cholera, dis_elephant, dis_csm,
dis_goiter, dis_buruli, dis_oncho, dis_other.

Create health service problem dummies (hp_*) from Q13:

hp_no_facility, hp_lack_personnel, hp_cost, hp_too_far,
hp_no_meds, hp_no_accomm, hp_inadequate, hp_other.

Define modal aggregators:

mode_with_tie_smallest() for categorical birth_location_raw.

mode_yes_priority() for binary campaign variables.

Aggregate to EA-level:

EA-level disease presence: dis_*_EA (1 if any community reports problem).

EA-level service problems: hp_*_EA.

Campaigns: imm_campaign_5yr_EA, antimal_campaign_5yr_EA.

birth_location_mode: EA-level modal birth location.

Save EA-level health context file:

cs4c_cleaned.dta.

Compute prevalence statistics and construct a core subset (cs4c_core) for regression with selected health variables (e.g., dis_malaria_EA, hp_cost_EA, etc.).

5.7. cs5b.dta – Agricultural Inputs & Services

Purpose: Construct EA-level variables capturing agricultural service and input availability.

Key steps:

Load cs5b.dta, remove exact duplicates.

Keep & rename:

EA_ID, extension_centre_raw, cooperative_raw, tractors_count_raw,
rice_husker_raw, chem_fertilizer_raw, pesticide_use_raw,
irrigated_fields_raw, sharecroppers_raw.

Drop region, district.

Recode yes/no to 1/0 for all binary input variables.

Create tractors_present_raw:

1 if tractors_count_raw > 0, 0 if tractors_count_raw == 0, NA otherwise.

Aggregate to EA-level using mode_yes_priority():

extension_centre, cooperative, tractors_present,
rice_husker, chem_fertilizer, pesticide_use,
irrigated_fields, sharecroppers.

Replace NA in rice_husker with 0 (treat missing as “no husker”).

Summarize NAs in key variables and save as cs5b_cleaned.dta.

6. EA-Level Merge (EA_master_community_allmodules.dta)

Script: Master_Community.R

Purpose: Merge all module-specific EA-level files into a single master file.

Key steps:

Load all cleaned .dta files:

cs1_cleaned.dta, cs2_cleaned.dta, cs3_cleaned.dta,
cs4a_cleaned.dta, cs4b_cleaned.dta, cs4c_cleaned.dta,
cs5b_cleaned.dta .

Standardize EA_ID as character in each dataset.

Check for duplicate EA_IDs in each file and warn if present.

Use purrr::reduce() and dplyr::full_join() to perform a full outer join on EA_ID, ensuring all EAs across modules are retained.

Replace NA with 0 for conceptually binary EA-level variables, including:

Disease dummies: dis_*_EA

Health service problems: hp_*_EA

Campaigns: imm_campaign_5yr_EA, antimal_campaign_5yr_EA

Agricultural inputs: extension_centre, cooperative, tractors_present,
rice_husker, chem_fertilizer, pesticide_use, irrigated_fields, sharecroppers

birth_location_mode (coded 0 if missing).

Save final master file:

EA_master_community_allmodules.dta.

